21/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country's chief negotiator on EU accession, Vasile Puscas, urged members of parliament Tuesday (20 April) to accelerate debate on legislation needed to complete domestic preparations for EU membership. Puscas reminded parliament's Committee on European Integration that an assessment of progress achieved in preparation for membership would be made in June, at a meeting of the EU-Romania Association Council. (Rompres - 20/04/04)
